OL,6,F"I carried on regardless," he said.
OL,7,F"I've been shot at, I've been blown
OL,8,Fup. I'm not going be intimidated by
OL,9,Fthreats like that."
OL,11,FThe men say the closer they got to the
OL,12,Ftruth ` that the Horizon system was
OL,13,Fdeeply flawed and that consequently
OL,14,Fthe convictions of hundreds of sub-
OL,15,Fpostmasters were unsafe ` then the
OL,16,Fmore the Post Office sabotaged their
OL,17,Finvestigation.
OL,19,F"They were limiting access to key
OL,20,Fdocuments. Key files. Failing to
OL,21,Fanswer questions," said Mr Henderson.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
