OL,6,FIt became clear the client was the
OL,7,Falso the culprit.
OL,9,F"They didn't want us to do the job
OL,10,Fthat we were appointed to do; which
OL,11,Fwas to seek the truth, regardless of
OL,12,Fthe consequences," he said.
OL,14,FTheir repeated warnings to the Post
OL,15,FOffice were ignored and Mr Warmington
OL,16,Ftook the decision to secretly tape
OL,17,Fconversations with senior executives.
OL,19,F"I no longer trusted them," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
