OL,6,F"What I saw in Paula and many others
OL,7,Fwas this compartmentalisation where
OL,8,Fdespite the clarity with which we'd
OL,9,Fexpressed the problems, about the
OL,10,Fprosecution practice and poor
OL,11,Finvestigations and so on, she seemed
OL,12,Fto be able to forget that.
OL,14,F"I think it was displaced by advice
OL,15,Fthat she obtained from lawyers."
OL,17,FMs Vennells has denied wrongdoing. In
OL,18,Fher three days of evidence to the
OL,19,Finquiry she claimed she too had been
OL,20,Fmisled by her staff.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
